The paper deals with optimization problems in Bayesian games, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The hardness results presented in the paper involve computational complexity, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses network routing games, which are a type of network optimization problem, indicating that the paper could be relevant to the sub-category of network economics (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the design of mechanisms to achieve desirable equilibria, which is a common theme in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
